page.title: 10LANDSCAPE AROUND SOUTHILL
page.content: The landscape in and around southill is very flat.There are a few hills near the public house .There is also a lot of hills and slopes in{SOUTHILL {PARK}.Most of the land is taken up by farming and agricultural land.Sheep also take up a bit of the land when they are grazing in the fields .Most of the land is on the {WHITBREAD {ESTATE.}Southill is taken up by about fifty percent trees,twenty percent houses and the fields take up about thirty percent of Southill.Some of the roads around Southill are very straight.There is an old disused railway which runs through the park and by-passes Southill itself.The roads that wind around Sothill are very small.There is one main road going though Southill but there are a few smaller roads leading onto the main road.
